Package: CSM
Title: Toolbox to analyze tissue images with spatial resolution
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Alvaro", family = "Lopez-Janeiro", email = "alopezj@unav.es", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5744-3115")),
    person(given = "Paulo", family = "Perez-Dominguez", email = "pperezdomin@unav.es", role = "ctb"),
    person(given = "Eduardo", family = "Miraval",email = "emiraval@unav.es", role = "ctb"),
    person(given = "Raluca", family = "Alexandru", email = "ralexandru@unav.es", role = "ctb"),
    person(given = "Carlos E.", family = "de Andrea",email = "ceandrea@unav.es", role = "ctb"))
Description: Contains functions to perform tissue spatial analysis. 
    Functions are organized in 7 modules. MODULE0 Generates cell and pixel level
    information and formats data. MODULE1 normalizes cell features. MODULE2
    thresholds features. MODULE3 performs cell phenotyping. MODULE4 analyzes 
    heterogeneity. MODULE5 performs cell-to-cell spatial interaction analysis.
    MODULE6 performs neighborhood analysis.
